{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:job.37",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 37,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 37",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 37 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:job.37.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:1",
      "text": "“Yes, at this my heart trembles, and is moved out of its place.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.37.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:2",
      "text": "Hear, oh, hear the noise of his voice, the sound that goes out of his mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.37.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:3",
      "text": "He sends it out under the whole sky, and his lightning to the ends of the earth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.37.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:4",
      "text": "After it a voice roars. He thunders with the voice of his majesty. He doesn’t hold back anything when his voice is heard.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.37.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:5",
      "text": "God thunders marvelously with his voice. He does great things, which we can ’t comprehend.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.37.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:6",
      "text": "For he says to the snow, ‘ Fall on the earth,’ likewise to the shower of rain, and to the showers of his mighty rain.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.37.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:7",
      "text": "He seals up the hand of every man, that all men whom he has made may know it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.37.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:8",
      "text": "Then the animals take cover, and remain in their dens.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.37.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:9",
      "text": "Out of its room comes the storm, and cold out of the north.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.37.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:10",
      "text": "By the breath of God, ice is given, and the width of the waters is frozen.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.37.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:11",
      "text": "Yes, he loads the thick cloud with moisture. He spreads abroad the cloud of his lightning.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.37.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:12",
      "text": "It is turned around by his guidance, that they may do whatever he commands them on the surface of the habitable world,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.37.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:13",
      "text": "whether it is for correction, or for his land, or for loving kindness, that he causes it to come.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.37.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:14",
      "text": "“Listen to this, Job. Stand still, and consider the wondrous works of God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.37.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:15",
      "text": "Do you know how God controls them, and causes the lightning of his cloud to shine?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.37.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:16",
      "text": "Do you know the workings of the clouds, the wondrous works of him who is perfect in knowledge?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.37.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:17",
      "text": "You whose clothing is warm when the earth is still by reason of the south wind?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.37.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:18",
      "text": "Can you, with him, spread out the sky, which is strong as a cast metal mirror?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.37.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:19",
      "text": "Teach us what we will tell him, for we can ’t make our case by reason of darkness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.37.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:20",
      "text": "Will it be told him that I would speak? Or should a man wish that he were swallowed up?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.37.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:21",
      "text": "Now men don’t see the light which is bright in the skies, but the wind passes, and clears them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.37.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:22",
      "text": "Out of the north comes golden splendor. With God is awesome majesty.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.37.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:23",
      "text": "We can ’t reach the Almighty. He is exalted in power. In justice and great righteousness, he will not oppress.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.37.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:24",
      "text": "Therefore men revere him. He doesn’t regard any who are wise of heart.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
